  "description": "Botrytis cinerea Pers. Fr. (teleomorph: Botryotinia fuckeliana) is a\n necrotrophic fungal pathogen that attacks a wide range of plants. This\n updated pathogen profile explores the extensive genetic diversity of B.\n cinerea, highlights the progress in genome sequencing, and provides\n current knowledge of genetic and molecular mechanisms employed by the\n fungus to attack its hosts. In addition, we also discuss recent innovative\n strategies to combat B. cinerea.",
